elem_dict.key: 517_823_351_63_Manufactured shelving usually doesn’t offer spacing flexibility and easy reconfiguration. Consider building your own utility  shelves  to fit the exact space you have available. Since you'll anchor it to the ceiling joists and the floor, it'll be sturdier under a heavy load than most freestanding garage shelves. You can also dress it up with the simple addition of side panels and stock trim molding on the face frame.
